#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:1
msgid "pyemscripten_2026_0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:3
msgid ""
"By default, all builds of the Pyodide runtime with Python 3.14 use the "
"`pyemscripten_2026_0` platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:6
msgid ""
"This section reflects the planned definition for the `pyemscripten_2026_0` "
"platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:9
msgid "Platform Specification"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:11
msgid "CPython and Emscripten Version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:13
msgid "**CPython**: 3.14"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:14
msgid "**Emscripten**: 5.0.3"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:16
msgid "Unwinding ABIs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:18
msgid ""
"C++ libraries are built with WebAssembly exception handling (`-fwasm-"
"exceptions`) and WebAssembly-based `setjmp`/`longjmp` (`-"
"sSUPPORT_LONGJMP=wasm`). To enable exceptions and `setjmp`/`longjmp`, `-"
"fwasm-exceptions` must be passed at compile time and link time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:23
msgid "Rust Toolchain"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:25
msgid ""
"When building Rust packages to target the `pyemscripten_2026_0` platform, "
"use Rust version 1.93.0 or later."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:28
msgid "Runtime Library Loading Path"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:30
msgid ""
"There is full support for `RPATH`. The dynamic loader will only load "
"dependencies that are properly specified on the `RPATH`, just being in `/lib/"
"python3.14/site-packages/wheel_name.libs` is not sufficient."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:34
msgid "Libraries Linked to the Main Binary"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:36
msgid "The following libraries are statically linked to the binary:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:38
msgid "`libegl.js`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:39
msgid "`libeventloop.js`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:40
msgid "`libGL`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:41
msgid "`libhtml5_webgl.js`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:42
msgid "`libhtml5.js`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:43
msgid "`liblz4`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:44
msgid "`libsdl.js`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:45
msgid "`libwebgl.js`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:46
msgid "`libwebsocket.js`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:47
msgid "`bzip2`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:48
msgid "`zlib`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:49
msgid "`sqlite3` version 3.39.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:50
msgid "`lzma` (xz) version 5.2.2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:52
msgid ""
"Aside from `sqlite3` and `lzma`, these libraries come from Emscripten ports "
"and the versions of the libraries are determined by the version of "
"Emscripten we build with. Any symbols from these static libraries may be "
"used by shared libraries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:57
msgid "Changes from pyemscripten_2025_0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:59
msgid "Platform Name"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:61
msgid "The platform name was changed from `pyodide` to `pyemscripten`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:63
msgid "Emscripten version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:65
msgid "Emscripten was upgraded from **4.0.9** to **5.0.3**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:67
msgid "Rust toolchain simplified"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:69
msgid ""
"In `pyemscripten_2025_0`, a Rust nightly was required with the unstable `-Z "
"emscripten-wasm-eh` flag and a custom sysroot. In `pyemscripten_2026_0`, "
"Rust 1.93.0 or later is sufficient — no custom sysroot or nightly-only flags "
"are needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:74
msgid ""
"Technically speaking, this is not a change to the platform. "
"`pyemscripten_2025_0` also works with stable Rust 1.93.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:77
msgid "Additional statically linked libraries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:79
msgid ""
"The following libraries are now statically linked to the interpreter in "
"addition to the Emscripten port libraries:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:82
msgid "`sqlite3` (3.39.0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/abi/314.md:83
msgid "`lzma` (xz) (5.2.2)"
msgstr ""
